  "Oct.   13\tFrom 12": "00 - 1:00 p.m., Telephony Services will reboot the back-up processor on the Cajun ATM Network.  This change is necessary to alleviate dropped calls in EB, ECS and 3AC due to an unstable environment on the back-up processor.   No impact is expected.",

{
  "At 11": "00 a.m., Enron Network Services will add routing protocols to the 155.251.16.0 network which currently bridges Gas Control from Houston to Omaha.  This change along with additional maintenance will result in disruption of service between Houston and Omaha for the Gas Control segment only.",
  "Bcc": "sue.rich@enron.com, center.ets@enron.com",
  "Cc": "sue.rich@enron.com, center.ets@enron.com",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Fri, 12 Oct 2001 10:26:43 -0700 (PDT)",
  "From": "center.ets@enron.com",
  "From 10": "00 p.m. through 10/14 at 2:00 a.m., Telephony services will perform their monthly maintenance and backups of the CMS and Conversant systems.  No impact to ETS users is expected although the Solution Center will not have access to their call management system during this time.",
  "From 11": "00 p.m. through 10/21 at 3:00 a.m., the EDI team will upgrade the QA-Test server, adding hard drives and memory resulting in a total outage for the EDI test environment.",
  "From 5": "00 - 6:00 p.m., the Messaging team will add all EES mail to route through mimesweeper.  No impact to ETS is expected.",
  "From 6": "00 p.m. through 10/14 at 6:00 p.m., the Unix group will perform maintenance on Adcupalpha.  The following application resides on this server: SAP / Project Sunrise.  This maintenance will result in a total disruption of access to these applications.",
  "From 7": "00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m., Facilities will complete the installation of Alarm and status controls on the new Humidifier Unit in 3450 and the new water detector system in the EB34 Data Center.  No impact is expected.",
  "From 8": "00 - 10:00 p.m., Enron Network Services will enable multicast or change filters to ENA WAN sites.  The sites affected include: Calgary, Chicago, Costa Mesa, Dublin, Hinsdale, NY Metals, Omaha, Portland, Toronto, and Washington DC.  There will be a slight disruption of service (a few seconds) to these WAN sites while the multicast changes are made.",
  "From 9": "00 a.m. - 2:00 p.m., Enron Network Services will migrate the switches for the printer networks on ECN 24 - ECN 38.  This is will effect the printers on each of these floors as the hubs are replaced.  The printers will be reconnected to the new cisco switches and tested to make sure they are back on the network.  No impact to ETS users is expected unless they reside on floors 24-38.",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c20542362.1075852964620.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "ETS and Corporate Change Control Items",

  "From 10": "00 a.m. - 1:00 p.m., the Messaging team will upgrade mailsweeper servers NAHOU-MSMSW03P and  NAHOU-MSMSW06P to version 4.2_8.  No impact is expected.",
  "From 11": "00 p.m. through 1/13 at 2:00 a.m., ENS backbone will replace the primary clock on the 172.16.7.0 server segment.  This switch is located in the old ECT 34th floor section of the raised floor.  All servers connected to this switch will have an outage of approximately three hours.  No impact to ETS users is expected.",
  "From 12": "00 p.m. through 1/15 at 12:00 p.m., the SAP team will move the XMS database from Seattle to Denver.  During this maintenance, the web-based XMS (employee expense) system will be unavailable.",
  "From 5": "00 p.m. through 1/27 at 5:00 p.m., the ETS server team will coordinate the move of the Envision system from 3AC to the Ardmore data facility.    During this move the Envision system will not be available.  Some of the applications affected by this outage include: Corporate-wide applications accessing the Envision web query, FileNet Panagon IDM Desktop, FileNet  IDM for R3, Panagon Capture professional.   "From": "center.ets@enron.com",
  "From 10": "30 - 11:30 p.m., the Omaha Infrastructure team will reconfigure the power connections for the Omaha Inverse MUX.  This change will result in a total disruption of IP communication between Omaha and Houston.  The outage should only last for a few minutes.  The maintenance time will be coordinated with the HotTap helpdesk to ensure processing has been completed.  All support staff whose applications are affected by this outage should communicate this change to their customers.  Please ensure they are aware of the possibility of an extended outage in the event the Inverse MUX does not properly re-establish communications.  LAT and DecNet communications for gas control will not be affected by this maintenance.",
  "From 6": "00 - 9:00 a.m., the Envision team will re-index the databases.  This outage will affect corporate-wide applications accessing the Envision web query, FileNet Panagon IDM Desktop, FileNet IDM for R3, Panagon Capture professional. Users will be able to access IBuyit and IPayit from SAP but will not be able to view invoices.",

  "Date": "Fri, 8 Feb 2002 13:48:39 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "center.ets@enron.com",
  "From 10": "30 - 11:30 p.m., the Omaha Infrastructure team will reconfigure the power connections for the Omaha Inverse MUX.  This change will result in a total disruption of IP communication between Omaha and Houston.  The outage should only last for a few minutes.  The maintenance time will be coordinated with the HotTap helpdesk to ensure processing has been completed.  All support staff whose applications are affected by this outage should communicate this change to their customers.  Please ensure they are aware of the possibility of an extended outage in the event the Inverse MUX does not properly re-establish communications.  LAT and DecNet communications for gas control will not be affected by this maintenance.",
  "From 5": "00 p.m. - 6:00 a.m., the Envision team will perform hardware maintenance on the Envision system.  This outage will affect corporate-wide applications accessing the Envision web query, FileNet Panagon IDM Desktop, FileNet IDM for R3, Panagon Capture professional. Users will be able to access IBuyit and IPayit from SAP but will not be able to view invoices.",

Support staff should ensure jobs going to the enron ftp server use ftp.enron.com.  Any questions about this maintenance, contact me at 713-853-3381 or 713-859-6676.",

  "Subject": "Severance Summary Plan Description - Domestic Pipeline Assets",
  "The severance plan provides that, under most circumstances, terminated employees would be eligible for two weeks of base pay for every full or partial year of service.  In the case of a termination due to reorganization, the minimum compensation would be eight weeks of pay and the maximum would be fifty-two weeks.  The details and restrictions to this plan are explained in the plan summary for your company's plan, which can be found on the ETS HR link on the Enron Transportation Services intranet site under \"ETS HR Manuals\".   "Message-ID": "\u003c9599083.1075860940018.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "KOMP Horticultural - Sale of Leased Plants",
  "The KOMP Horticultural contract for the maintenance of leased floor plants has been cancelled.  Plant maintenance is not being performed on the leased plants in the Enron Building on floors 3 through 49.  Rather than removing the plants from the building, KOMP Horticultural has chosen to offer the plants to Enron employees for sale.  On January 16th from 11": "00 AM to 2:00 PM, KOMP will have a table on the south side of the plaza, by the up escalator, for those employees interested in purchasing a plant. At the time of purchase, KOMP will give a special sticker to place on the container of the sold plant (do not bring plants to the plaza for purchase).  Plants will not be allowed to be removed from the building unless they have the KOMP sold sticker on the container.",
  "The following guidelines must be followed": "",

{
  "At 5": "00 p.m., the Corporate Security team will remove access to CORPHOU-DC07 (172.23.226.23, primary/secondary DNS) and NAHOU-NSWN03 (172.23.226.24, primary/secondary WINS) from devices within ECN.   All servers/workstations/equipment using these for WINS/DNS must have their settings changed. Use 172.16.7.120 for DNS and 172.16.7.116 for WINS in their place by this 5/01.",
  "Beginning today through 3/19, the Corporate Security team will replace the GRC.dat file in W": "\\scripts\\UpdateGRC and W:\\scripts\\logon\\Win2000\\original to point NAV clients on nahou-apnav01 to nahou-apnav02 (only about 650 left).  No impact is expected.",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Thu, 14 Mar 2002 13:44:05 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "center.ets@enron.com",
  "From 10": "00 - 11:00 p.m., Telephony Services will perform the monthly maintenance on the CMS (Call management) systems.  This maintenance affects only call center reporting.  No impact to users is expected.",
  "From 11": "00 - 11:15 a.m., the Corporate Security group will remove the svceu_SAPConnect account from CORP Domain Admins group.  No impact is expected.",
  "From 2": "00 - 4:00 p.m., the Blackberry Network Team will perform maintenance on a component of the Blackberry Network.  Some customers may experience delays in receiving messages.  It is also possible that messages sent from he Blackberry may be returned.  Returned messages can be resent after the maintenance is complete.",
  "From 4": "00 - 6:00 p.m.., the Unix Team will upgrade the Time server.  Timex.ect.enron.com which is now on a Unix desktop network will be moved to a production network and to Netra T1 hardware. It would be doing the same activity as Rolex which was replaced on Monday. All clients are now pointing to new Rolex server \u0026 Timex.  No impact is expected.",
  "From 5": "00 - 6:00 p.m., the Corporate Security team will change the DHCP scopes to update the secondary WINS and DNS entries.  This change will affect workstations that get their IP addresses via DHCP.  All scopes are renewed on a 24-hour basis so all changes should be completed by 3/19.  No impact is expected.",
  "From 8": "00 p.m. through 3/17 at 6:00 p.m., the Corporate Security team will re-enable the File Replication Service on all Corporate domain controllers.  This change is necessary to replicate security policies.   FRS will be started on Corp DCs one at a time, watching to be sure replication completes.  Brief outages of Corp.enron.com security policies and possibly Exchange may occur.  The Messaging team will be notified if replication causes problems.  Support staff whose applications experience problems due to FRS should contact the solution center at ext. 54745.",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c326824.1075860950694.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "ETS and Corporate Change Control",
  "X-FileName": "ldonoho (Non-Privileged).pst",
  "X-Folder": "\\Lindy_Donoho_Mar2002_1\\Donoho, Lindy\\Inbox\\Junk File",

{
  "At 5": "00 p.m., the Corporate Security team will remove access to CORPHOU-DC07 (172.23.226.23, primary/secondary DNS) and NAHOU-NSWN03 (172.23.226.24, primary/secondary WINS) from devices within ECN.   All servers/workstations/equipment using these for WINS/DNS must have their settings changed. Use 172.16.7.120 for DNS and 172.16.7.116 for WINS in their place by this 5/01.",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Thu, 21 Mar 2002 08:34:07 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "center.ets@enron.com",
  "From 5": "00 p.m. through 3/24 at 7:00 a.m., the Envision system will be taken offline to perform backups.  Users will not be able to access information located on Envision during this maintenance.",
  "From 7": "00 - 8:00 p.m., the Messaging team will update the virus engine on Mailsweeper servers. This will be done on a monthly basis for better protection against new viruses.  No impact is expected.",
  "From 8": "00 - 11:45 p.m., the Corporate Security team will re-enable the File Replication Service on all Corporate domain controllers.  This change is necessary to replicate security policies.   FRS will be started on Corp DCs one at a time, watching to be sure replication completes.  Brief outages of Corp.enron.com security policies and possibly Exchange may occur.  The Messaging team will be notified if replication causes problems.  Support staff whose applications experience problems due to FRS should contact the solution center at ext. 54745.",
  "From 9": "00 a.m. through 4/5 at 3:00 p.m., the Corporate server team will make WINS/DNS changes on all servers to reflect the new server settings.  Devices that require a reboot will be submitted via a separate change control.   Some impact may occur during these changes and that information will be forwarded as it becomes available.",
  "Future Changes": "",

{
  "At the meeting yesterday, SoCalGas outlined their plan for implementing the unbundling of their backbone system including a proposed timeline which will be filed at the CPUC on Jan. 17, 2002.  Lad Lorenz state that the proposal is \"not cast in concrete\" and invited comments at the meeting as well as in response to the filing.  However as you might expect, when some customers expressed their concern with the timeline being too short, SoCal made no offer to push some of the dates out into the future and stuck with their proposal.  All of the proposed dates are their best estimate for timing as variables such as the system requirements may cause delays and rescheduling of some portions of the implementation plan.  Key items and dates are as follows": "",

  "As reported in Gas Daily today, the CPUC has issued a report assessing the state's gas infrastructure of the three major utilities in California.  Their conclusion is that the natural gas transportation and storage systems are adequate to provide seasonally reliable amounts of competitively priced natural gas to residential, commercial, industrial and electric generation customers.  Therefore they recommend that the Power Authority should not finance any new natural gas projects.  Other conclusions": "conservation will reduce demand on the infrastructure, improved coordination between electric and gas operations can enhance reliability, and the CPUC should continue to evaluate the need for gas infrastructure expansions.   "Sent": "Thursday, July 05, 2001 3:02 PM",
  "Subject": "Transwestern Pipeline [TWP] (La Plata) Colorado Sales \u0026 Use Tax Audit - Summary and Status",
  "The auditor has informed us that compressor fuel used by TWP is taxable.  We have confirmed that other taxpayers are also paying this tax.  At the conclusion of the audit, the auditor said that TWP may assign a reasonable value to the compressor fuel.  We will discuss the": "",
  "The following are potential exposures and issues": "",

  "Date": "Thu, 25 Oct 2001 07:11:48 -0700 (PDT)",
  "From": "center.ets@enron.com",
  "From 1": "45 a.m. - 2:15 a.m., sysAdmiral master system will be shut down during the time change from Daylight Savings Time to Standard Time. This is being done as a precautionary measure due to a potential sysAdmiral bug.",
  "From 10": "30 p.m. - 11:00 p.m., Fiber maintenance will be performed in the 41st floor wiring closet. This fiber connects the 41st floor wiring closet to the 41st floor server room.  Connectivity between servers in the 41st floor server room and the Enron network will be disrupted. The cabling engineer believes the change should take less than 30 minutes.  If he runs into a problem, the outage could possibly be two hours.",
  "From 3": "00 - 9:00 p.m., Trizechan Properties has scheduled a shutdown of all electrical service at 3 Allen Center.  Enron Network Services will power down the 3AC network infrastructure between 3:30-4:00.  There will be no network access during the electrical maintenance and the outage will continue until ENS is able to power up all of the networking devices.  If you need access to 3AC anytime Saturday, you will need to contact Trizechan Properties beforehand with your security information.  Anyone who attempts to enter the building on Saturday that is not on the list will be denied access. 3AC Telco and Voicemail services will be unavailable during the outage period.",
  "From 6": "00 - 6:30 p.m., ENS will be opening a DMZ firewall port to allow users on HOTTAPTS11 to run the NBPL Oracle application on nb2175.nbp.enron.com.",
  "From 7": "00 - 9:00 p.m., Server HR-DB-4 will be shutdown to replace disks. Affected apps will be all HRGlobal applications including but not limited to Global Launch Zone, HRGIS, GCS, eHRonline, etc.",

  "California": "",
  "California Infrastructure.  FERC staff made a presentation at the March 13th meeting indicating that in-state capacity is insufficient to meet peak power demand.  Staff indicated that only two favorable factors beyond the state's control that have changed since the power blackouts of a year ago": "the economy and the weather.  With recession, energy demand is down and therefore prices are near a five-year low.  Heavy snowpack in the Pacific Northwest/California areas will provide sufficient hydropower for the upcoming summer peak periods.
